getTaskUser

public String getTaskUser()
Description copied from interface: LightTaskInstance
Returns the user assigned for the task.
Check before calling this method if a user has been assigned with LightTaskInstance.isTaskAssigned() method. The assigned user depends on:
  • the user assigned for the task when the task has been initially created
  • actions performed on the task such as start, suspend, resume, assign. Update list contains all information on these recorded updates (assign update, state update).

Specified by:
getTaskUser in interface LightTaskInstance
Returns:
The user assigned for the task.
